  "texts": [
    "The risk to produce such errors is especially salient in domains that require expert-level knowledge such as the biomedical domain.",
    "Taking Figure 1 for example, \"NF-kappa B\" is incorrectly labeled as \"RNA\" type and \"endothelia cells\" is identified with wrong span.",
    "Erroneous prediction is a significant threat to their application in domains where high precision is required (Dai, 2021; Karim et al., 2023).",
    "In this paper, we seek to minimize these errors by incorporating knowledge into the inference process.",
    "Figure 1 suggests that knowledge can serve as a useful evidence for humans to verify that the type of \"NF-kappa B\" is \"protein\"."
  ],
